My discord tag comes from a little tradition I made for myself Growing up, my family would only have soda during special occasions or to cheer each other up. I don’t like talking about it much, but I don’t have a very good memory- it’s gotten worse as I’ve gotten older After a while, I couldn’t keep all the cans and bottles so I started to just collect the tabs and bottle caps instead Hence the name “ShanTheSodaCan” In honor of the good times I’ve had

I struggled in school for a while since I wasn’t naturally gifted, and I worried I wasn’t gonna really go far Once I was eventually able to develop study habits that worked, I soared to the top of the ranks academically and I took a great deal of pride in that My academic status granted me friendships that weren’t achievable at first, and I was given better opportunities. As a result, I started to gain a pretty unhealthy attachment to my academic standing. The basis of my worth started to get rooted in education and being perceived as intelligent- I worried losing that perception would cost me greatly This began to manifest in unhealthy ways- mainly lashing out at people who would question my intelligence to any degree. I became very domineering and nasty towards people who made me feel less than and it started to consume my personality. It got so bad at one point that my parents were called into the school and lectured about my behavior You saw a very mild version of it last night- frustration and some resentment towards people continuously shooting down my ideas. Mild or not though, I still feel bad for it I recognize why little Shannon Renee behaved the way she did and I give her grace for that, but I’m older now and should know better I mentioned it at the beginning of my confessional, but I am trying to teach myself that it is okay to not be the best, and that accepting yourself where you are at is a far better feeling than any ascension to perfection This serves as a moment of that growth
